params.minValue: Revert if valueReceived is smaller than this.

addValue(address,uint16,uint128,uint128).details: Use approvals to limit slippage, or you can wrap this with a helper contract which validates the requiredBalances are small enough according to some logic.

params.maxRequired: Revert if required balance is greater than this. (0 indicates no restriction).

params.maxValue: Revert if valueGiven is larger than this. (Not enforced if zero.)

removeValue(address,uint16,uint128,uint1.details: Wrap this with a helper contract which validates the received balances are sufficient.

params.minReceive: Revert if removedBalance is smaller than this.

addSingleForValue(address,uint16,address.notice: Add exactly this much of the given token for value in the given closure.

addValue(address,uint16,uint128,uint128).notice: Add exactly this much value to the given closure by providing all tokens involved.

addValueSingle(address,uint16,uint128,ui.notice: Add exactly this much value to the given closure by providing a single token.

queryValue(address,uint16).notice: Return the held value balance and earnings by an address in a given closure.

removeSingleForValue(address,uint16,addr.notice: Remove exactly this much of the given token for value in the given closure.

removeValue(address,uint16,uint128,uint1.notice: Remove exactly this much value to the given closure and receive all tokens involved.

removeValueSingle(address,uint16,uint128.notice: Remove exactly this much value to the given closure by receiving a single token.
